Former White House aide MichaelDeaver, a long-time confidant of President Reagan, has beenindicted on charges of lying about his contacts as a Washingtonlobbyist with top U.S. Government officials.    The five-count perjury indictment charged that Deaver liedin sworn testimony to Congress and before the grand juryinvestigating his business affairs.    Deaver, who resigned as deputy White House chief of staffin 1985 to open a lobbying firm, faces a maximum penalty of 25years in prison if convicted. Immediately after the indictmentwas announced Reagan issued a statement wishing Deaver well. Reuter&#3;